cyclone.name: FRED
cyclone.current_location: about 235 miles south of Panama City, Florida
cyclone.trajectory: tracking north-northwest across the eastern Gulf of Mexico, expected to turn north and come ashore in the western Florida Panhandle, then move inland across Alabama-Georgia and into the southern Appalachians later in the week
cyclone.expected_landfall_location: western Florida Panhandle (near or east of Panama City, FL)

weather_observation.watch_coast: Tropical-storm watches extend from the Alabama/Florida border to Navarre, FL
weather_observation.warning_coast: Tropical-storm warnings from Navarre, FL to the Wakulla/Jefferson County line; storm-surge warnings Indian Pass to Yankeetown, FL
weather_observation.impacted_coast: Northern Gulf Coast from Alabama eastward through the Florida Big Bend
weather_observation.rainfall: Remnant moisture could bring 1â€“2 inches of rain to southern New Jersey late in the week, but widespread flooding is not expected.
weather_observation.other_hazards: A low-end risk of brief, weak inland tornadoes cannot be ruled out if remnant Fred tracks close to the Mid-Atlantic, but the probability at the port is very low.
